sentence: If I remember correctly the underlying problem was (is?) an ABI incompatibility between clang and gcc in the way arguments are packed on the stack on some optimization cases (i.e. I was surprised that just reordering the arguments was solving the problem). I don't remember the details (@Axel-Naumann might) but reducing the number of arguments or passing only numerical (and pointer) type might help.
